                            <comment id="13026316" author="jake.mannix" created="Thu, 28 Apr 2011 15:14:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;How does this compare to what is in the latest patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-458&quot; title=&quot;The LDA output does not include the topic-probability distribution per document (p(z|d)). It outputs only the topics and corresponding words.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-458&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-458&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13026901" author="vavasilev" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2011 09:11:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jake,&lt;br/&gt;
Didn&apos;t know about &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-458&quot; title=&quot;The LDA output does not include the topic-probability distribution per document (p(z|d)). It outputs only the topics and corresponding words.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-458&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-458&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
When I took a look, seems that your patch collects the same information that I extract via LDAVectorizer. May be it is really a better approach to make this part of the LDA inference process. &lt;br/&gt;
However, I think, it is worth having in the end set of vectors (a vector per document) which can directly be used for clustering with some of the existing algorithms (KMeans, Canopy, etc.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One question: I noticed that you normalize the Gamma vector before writing it - why is that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13027062" author="jake.mannix" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2011 17:27:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Vasil,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-458&quot; title=&quot;The LDA output does not include the topic-probability distribution per document (p(z|d)). It outputs only the topics and corresponding words.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-458&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-458&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; does end up with a set of vectors, one per document, which live on HDFS in a sequence file of IntWritable -&amp;gt; VectorWritable (located at: ), and this is directly in the form required to construct a DistributedRowMatrix, if any further matrix/clustering operations are desired.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  The vectors are (L_1) normalized so that the resultant vector entries can be interpreted properly as probabilities: gamma_doc_x.get(topic_index_i) returns the probability that document x will produce a term from topic i.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
