                            <comment id="13037784" author="srowen" created="Mon, 23 May 2011 09:05:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Question: do I read correctly from the commit log that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-682&quot; title=&quot;The LDA output does not include the topic-probability distribution per document (p(z|d)). It outputs only the topics and corresponding words.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-682&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-682&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-683&quot; title=&quot;LDA Vectorization&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-683&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-683&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; are fixed, and for 0.5?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
